appeng.api.storage

Interface ICellRegistry


  • public interface ICellRegistry
    Storage Cell Registry, used for specially implemented cells, if you just want to make a item act like a cell, or new cell with different bytes, then you should probably consider IStorageCell instead its considerably simpler. Do not Implement, obtained via IAppEngApi.getCellRegistry()

      • getCellInventory

        @Nullable
<T extends IAEStack<T>> ICellInventoryHandler<T> getCellInventory(net.minecraft.item.ItemStack is,
                                                                            ISaveProvider host,
                                                                            IStorageChannel<T> chan)
        returns an ICellInventoryHandler for the provided item by querying all registered handlers.
        Parameters:
        is - item with inventory handler
        host - can be null. If provided, the host is responsible for persisting the cell content.
